What is the Jupyter Network ?

The Jupyter Network is a suite of decentralized applications (dApps) built on the BSC Blockchain.

What is $IOM ?

$IOM is a BEP20 compatible token, secured by OpenZeppelin that can be used in all Ethereum wallets that support the Binance Smart Chain. $IOM token is non-mintable, having a 1'000'000'000 total supply.

Where can i get $IOM ?

You can get your $IOM from Pancakeswap, Tokpie or later on from Jupyterswap.

Energy Efficiency

The BNB chain combines both delegated PoS and PoA to achieve network consensus and maintain blockchain security.

Thats why BNB Chain is one of the fastest and most efficient blockchains.
